<br>
Personally I'd like to see skin spells added at level 4 (Malachite (5 silver), 12 pts max protection) and 12 (Turquoise (1 gold), 30 pts max protection).  This would make Wizards more survivable at those levels without being overpowering in any sense.<br>
<br>
Put a mez-like minimum duration on Enstil so it acts like a very reliable root but has no soloing use.<br>
<br>
Turn Bonds of Force and Atol's Spirit Shackles into AE Root spells, if we are better in groups we hardly need to solo as well.<br>
<br>
Add in a faster-casting Gate spell for Wizards only.  If we are meant by Verant to be superior at teleporting, why do we have such a slow teleport home?  This would help us in emergencies as well.<br>
<br>
Fix the self-only ports to work past impediments and be able to port up (but only a limited amount, so you can't port on top of places that could be exploited easily).<br>
<br>
Add in a spell that eliminates environmental clutter for Wizards (no snow, fog, etc) at level 29.<br>
<br>
Add in a spell that makes water, blood, etc clear to see through at level 16.<br>
<br>
Lower Chill Sight to level 29 and Heat Sight to level 8.<br>
<br>
Put in a MR self buff, we get all the others but not MR, why is that?  Yes, the shielding spells raise Magic Resistances... just like they do for Enchanters, who can cast magic resistance on others.  It just fits the 'self sufficient world traveller' image Verant seems to have of Wizards and is consistent with the present spell list.<br>
<br>
That's just little stuff to jazz up the class and make it more survivable at lower levels.  It would mean we would be slightly more useful in groups as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unicolheartsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nicol Heartsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 751<br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/19/02 2:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What remains to be done?</span><hr size=1> The anti-fog and see through water are pretty cool ideas, and actually something that we would have claim to as the seekers of knowledge.  Interesting.  Unlikely to happen, but interesting, grim.<br>
